cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) categories, as it deals with the task of Vision-Language Navigation (VLN) where agents learn to navigate following natural language instructions. Additionally, the paper introduces a framework with self-supervised auxiliary reasoning tasks, which involves reasoning and decision-making, making it likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, since the task involves navigation, it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category.
